Director: YAMASHITA ATSUHIRO
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

15
00:01:05,541 --> 00:01:05,862
Director: YAMASHITA ATSUHIRO
Zutto mukashi no koto no yoda ne
<i>Always seems like a thing of the past</i>

16
00:01:05,862 --> 00:01:15,571
Zutto mukashi no koto no yoda ne
<i>Always seems like a thing of the past</i>

17
00:01:15,571 --> 00:01:20,274
Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
<i>Clouds passing over a flowing river</i>

18
00:01:20,274 --> 00:01:25,928
<i>My business hours start from midnight to 7 am.</i>
Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
<i>Clouds passing over a flowing river</i>

19
00:01:25,928 --> 00:01:30,300
<i>People call my restaurant 'the late night diner.'</i>

20
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:33,819
[MESHIYA]

21
00:01:33,819 --> 00:01:38,050
<i>Do customers come? You ask...
There's quite a number who do.</i>

22
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:48,920
<i>Wabi-Sabi Subs presents:</i>
<b>SHINYA SHOKUDO Season 3</b>
EP 8: "Sauteed Burdock Root..."

23
00:02:01,190 --> 00:02:03,560
Wouldn't it be better to rewrite your menu?

24
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:06,460
Change it to something like
"Porkish flavored miso soup."

25
00:02:09,490 --> 00:02:11,400
Or "Pork soup impersonation."

26
00:02:28,090 --> 00:02:29,560
Da hell's your problem?

27
00:02:30,770 --> 00:02:35,310
Gen-san, do you like "kinpira" (sauteed veggies)
because you're a "chinpira" (thug)?

28
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:42,770
Just let it go. She doesn't know anything at all
about you getting teased in the past.

29
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:46,520
I'm sorry if I said something rude.

30
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:48,750
'Cause you're a woman,
I'll let ya off da hook.

31
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:53,080
If you were a man, I'd make you
bungee-jump off the Sky Tree.

32
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,690
Master, give Gen-san a drink...

33
00:02:56,860 --> 00:02:57,880
I don't want it!

34
00:02:57,880 --> 00:03:00,060
But let me treat you as a way of apologizing...

35
00:03:00,270 --> 00:03:03,030
Gen-chan doesn't drink.
Despite having a scary face...

36
00:03:03,030 --> 00:03:04,820
Be quiet.

37
00:03:04,820 --> 00:03:06,560
But the beer...

38
00:03:07,660 --> 00:03:09,270
He hasn't touched it.

39
00:03:13,990 --> 00:03:15,910
What do you call that kind of thing again...?

40
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:20,130
Even though someone has a scary face,
yet he doesn't drink...

41
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:24,300
- It's "deceptive appearance"
(also, "mere front"), right?
- Ya wanna have a go, punk!!

42
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:29,050
You have till after I finish eatin to think of
the Buddhist name you want on your grave! Baldy!

43
00:03:29,050 --> 00:03:32,350
I'm a Christian! I will repent!

44
00:03:32,350 --> 00:03:34,420
What're ya sayin! I don't get cha!

45
00:03:34,470 --> 00:03:35,290
I'm sorry!

46
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,550
Don't try changin your religion!

47
00:03:41,420 --> 00:03:43,330
Do you have Kinpira Gobo*?
(*chopped burdock root,
sauteed in sugar and soy sauce)

48
00:03:43,502 --> 00:03:44,442
I do.

49
00:03:44,610 --> 00:03:47,640
I'm glad. Then Kinpira Gobo and
unheated alcohol right away please.

50
00:03:47,740 --> 00:03:48,710
Sure thing.

51
00:04:04,060 --> 00:04:05,160
Thanks for waiting.

52
00:04:06,420 --> 00:04:09,430
This really is the way
that kinpira must be made.

53
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,260
Why is that?

54
00:04:12,530 --> 00:04:15,490
'Cause it won't get crunchy unless
you cut it into strips.

55
00:04:16,620 --> 00:04:21,140
I thought so too... Kinpira
should be shredded, right?

56
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:23,740
You like Kinpira, too?

57
00:04:29,580 --> 00:04:32,920
Long time no see! Ichikawa-sensei.

58
00:04:33,756 --> 00:04:36,906
You taught English at
Kawakita High School, didn't you?

59
00:04:37,540 --> 00:04:38,860
I did, actually...

60
00:04:38,860 --> 00:04:42,990
I'm Hayashi Gen.
You were our adviser in the handball club.

61
00:04:44,041 --> 00:04:46,971
Are you the Gen-kun who was always
getting into fights?

62
00:04:48,529 --> 00:04:51,969
I had eyebrows back then.

63
00:05:00,180 --> 00:05:04,280
I didn't recognize you!
You've become quite a man, huh!

64
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:06,180
How many years has it been?

65
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:09,780
I don't know. I'm just a dumb guy.

66
00:05:12,273 --> 00:05:13,983
No way!

67
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:24,730
Even though I call myself an interpreter,
compared to entertaining clients,
it's more like doing a guide's work.

68
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:29,420
Well, your level is really different.

69
00:05:29,420 --> 00:05:34,483
While guys like me live an obscure life
in some rundown Shinjuku area such as this.

70
00:05:34,483 --> 00:05:36,630
Do you know, Baldy?

71
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:40,620
She lives in New York,
the capital of USA.

72
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:43,850
Washington DC is the capital of the US...

73
00:05:43,850 --> 00:05:44,920
Hah?

74
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,560
It's New York.

75
00:05:48,460 --> 00:05:50,827
Coming home for the first time in 10 years...

76
00:05:50,827 --> 00:05:54,350
I didn't expect to be reunited with you
straight away.

77
00:05:54,867 --> 00:05:57,297
I wonder if this is some kind of fate.

78
00:05:58,927 --> 00:06:01,797
You say you live with
a person over there...

79
00:06:02,630 --> 00:06:04,150
Is it your husband?

80
00:06:04,150 --> 00:06:06,550
A female friend who's a
co-worker of mine.

81
00:06:06,710 --> 00:06:08,950
Did you think that it would be pathetic
if I were still single at this age?

82
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:10,450
Of course not!

83
00:06:12,844 --> 00:06:14,134
You...

84
00:06:15,300 --> 00:06:17,190
...haven't changed at all since those days.

85
00:06:17,190 --> 00:06:19,870
My goodness, you've become
quite a flatterer, too huh.

86
00:06:21,921 --> 00:06:23,571
But I'm glad.

87
00:06:24,100 --> 00:06:26,410
Gen-kun, let's go to one more bar.

88
00:06:27,396 --> 00:06:28,466
Okay!

89
00:06:30,110 --> 00:06:33,180
He was such a handful,
what happened afterwards.

90
00:06:33,401 --> 00:06:36,991
Gen-kun took me to a good bar
that he said he knows but...

91
00:06:36,990 --> 00:06:38,890
I love you!!

92
00:06:39,038 --> 00:06:42,000
Gen-kun, sit straight or you'll fall.

93
00:06:43,459 --> 00:06:44,819
I said it!

94
00:06:45,959 --> 00:06:47,790
Kosuzu-chan, another glass...

95
00:06:47,790 --> 00:06:49,050
That's enough.

96
00:06:49,607 --> 00:06:51,417
Why say that?

97
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:54,940
Don't you know that this
is how much I love you?!

98
00:06:55,203 --> 00:06:56,473
Gen-chan!

99
00:06:56,869 --> 00:07:00,949
Lower your voice. You're
disturbing the other customers.

100
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:04,870
Besides, your teacher won't
like you, you know.

101
00:07:04,870 --> 00:07:06,790
But I love her so much!

102
00:07:06,790 --> 00:07:07,420
Ouch!

103
00:07:08,444 --> 00:07:10,554
If you call yourself a man, shape up!

104
00:07:15,070 --> 00:07:16,800
Please do it again.

105
00:07:18,554 --> 00:07:23,694
Please beat some sense into me! Please!

106
00:07:24,660 --> 00:07:26,380
Please!

107
00:07:28,270 --> 00:07:30,280
Then what happened?

108
00:07:30,577 --> 00:07:35,550
I had no choice so I was forced to
get him out of the bar and let him
sleep at the hotel I'm staying.

109
00:07:35,550 --> 00:07:37,920
He was puking until daybreak.

110
00:07:41,550 --> 00:07:42,790
Welcome.

111
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:44,790
He's my companion.

112
00:07:45,070 --> 00:07:46,390
Good evening.

113
00:07:46,390 --> 00:07:49,830
My homeroom teacher in high school
has turned into a middle aged fogey.

114
00:07:49,830 --> 00:07:51,550
He's my idol teacher.

115
00:07:51,550 --> 00:07:53,630
Like yesterday, only the other way around.

116
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:56,110
Yeah. Master, can we stay there.

117
00:07:56,110 --> 00:07:57,550
And can you give him another glass.

118
00:07:57,550 --> 00:07:58,470
Sure thing.

119
00:07:58,470 --> 00:07:59,370
Sorry I'm late.

120
00:08:06,510 --> 00:08:09,080
I made reservations in Atami.

121
00:08:09,470 --> 00:08:10,620
That's great.

122
00:08:11,590 --> 00:08:12,490
Excuse me.

123
00:08:17,510 --> 00:08:23,420
<i>"This was the only time, I felt sincerely
relieved that Gen-chan wasn't around."</i>

124
00:08:30,679 --> 00:08:33,739
I'm so lost, there's so much to choose from.

125
00:08:34,270 --> 00:08:38,510
I guess folks over there prefer
flashy patterns, don't they?

126
00:08:38,550 --> 00:08:41,150
Is your work really okay
about you being here?

127
00:08:41,594 --> 00:08:44,244
It's really no problem.
Don't worry about it.

128
00:08:45,572 --> 00:08:46,912
How about this one.

129
00:08:47,550 --> 00:08:50,160
Sparklers, huh...

130
00:08:51,670 --> 00:08:53,230
It's too simple, isn't it.

131
00:08:54,058 --> 00:08:58,848
How about fireworks...
with a more explosive "bang!" pattern.

132
00:08:59,506 --> 00:09:03,710
Oh, right. Since that person's a cat lover,
maybe a cat pattern will do.

133
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:06,270
Oh, if it's animals,
there's some over there.

134
00:09:14,647 --> 00:09:20,917
Nice, it's like flowers blooming in the shadows...
so ephemeral.

135
00:09:22,767 --> 00:09:25,147
Give it to me. I want to see it, too.

136
00:09:25,646 --> 00:09:27,096
Hey, don't dirty it.

137
00:09:28,447 --> 00:09:32,067
Oh, how cute!

138
00:09:32,527 --> 00:09:36,807
Wonder if it really suits Gen-chan.
Anyway...

139
00:09:36,807 --> 00:09:39,037
...it suits me, doesn't it?

140
00:09:43,352 --> 00:09:46,652
Gen-chan, does your teacher know
your line of work?

141
00:09:47,607 --> 00:09:49,547
Told her I'm into liberal employment.*
(*Like free lance or self-employed).

142
00:09:49,727 --> 00:09:54,287
Well, the yakuza is like liberal employment
in a way so it's not a lie. Right?

143
00:09:54,287 --> 00:09:58,287
What a woman hates the most is
a guy keeping secrets from her.

144
00:09:58,287 --> 00:10:03,007
I know that. I'm just waiting
for the right time to tell her.

145
00:10:03,807 --> 00:10:04,867
Thank you.

146
00:10:05,287 --> 00:10:07,797
When is your teacher going back?

147
00:10:08,248 --> 00:10:12,768
She said she'll be here for two weeks,
I think that was 4 to 5 days ago.

148
00:10:13,558 --> 00:10:15,268
Aren't you gonna call her now?

149
00:10:16,127 --> 00:10:17,677
She's busy.

150
00:10:17,687 --> 00:10:21,777
She goes out every night with old friends, and has
to take care of them when they get too drunk.

151
00:10:22,047 --> 00:10:25,187
It sounds like she came back home
to say goodbye or something...

152
00:10:26,367 --> 00:10:27,517
What does that mean?

153
00:10:28,687 --> 00:10:34,527
Either way, you have no choice
but to wait for your turn.

154
00:10:41,044 --> 00:10:46,214
<i>After three days,
Gen-chan's turn finally came.</i>

155
00:10:49,349 --> 00:10:50,669
Tastes good, right?

156
00:10:51,390 --> 00:10:52,310
Yeah.

157
00:10:53,837 --> 00:10:55,947
You're not gonna drink today, huh.

158
00:10:59,927 --> 00:11:04,387
I'm sorry. You saw my disgraceful behavior
the other day.

159
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:11,920
Hello.

160
00:11:12,197 --> 00:11:16,467
Yeah... I'm eating now.
Okay, I'll call you later.

161
00:11:19,549 --> 00:11:22,599
Don't mind me, I'm fine.
I'll just eat and go home anyway.

162
00:11:22,847 --> 00:11:28,567
It's not that. I was planning to go to Atami tomorrow
with someone but I can't contact him at all.

163
00:11:28,567 --> 00:11:29,977
I guess it's off.

164
00:11:31,517 --> 00:11:33,847
Is he your boyfriend?

165
00:11:34,287 --> 00:11:38,527
A guy from my past.
Anyway, his wife is scary.

166
00:11:39,860 --> 00:11:41,820
Wonder what I should do now...

167
00:11:50,037 --> 00:11:50,707
Um...

168
00:11:57,443 --> 00:11:59,063
I wonder if I'm okay...?

169
00:12:01,755 --> 00:12:02,965
...to go to Atami...

170
00:12:06,767 --> 00:12:08,387
With you?

171
00:12:17,607 --> 00:12:19,997
Are you okay with that? Going with such a hag.

172
00:12:25,313 --> 00:12:26,813
Of course, it's fine.

173
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:30,410
You ain't a hag at all!

174
00:12:32,709 --> 00:12:35,579
Imma kill anyone who calls you that!

175
00:12:36,327 --> 00:12:39,017
He's even a handful here, huh? Master.

176
00:12:39,727 --> 00:12:41,887
It's not just with his school teacher.

177
00:12:47,167 --> 00:12:48,257
Thank you.

178
00:12:49,367 --> 00:12:51,497
Don't be late tomorrow, okay?

179
00:12:52,660 --> 00:12:54,390
I'm not a kid anymore.

180
00:12:54,620 --> 00:12:57,860
Yeah. Good night.

181
00:12:58,621 --> 00:13:00,161
Good night.

182
00:13:01,238 --> 00:13:05,138
I'm sorry. I had a bit of a problem at work...

183
00:13:05,469 --> 00:13:08,949
But it's okay. I can go with you tomorrow.

184
00:13:10,820 --> 00:13:12,040
A friend of yours?

185
00:13:13,927 --> 00:13:15,617
A former student.

186
00:13:16,847 --> 00:13:19,157
I see. I'll help you to your room.

187
00:13:21,167 --> 00:13:22,497
Are you angry?

188
00:13:23,687 --> 00:13:25,927
Of course, she's angry, Senpai.

189
00:13:28,447 --> 00:13:33,667
She's been waiting for your call.

190
00:13:35,438 --> 00:13:36,678
So please...

191
00:13:37,767 --> 00:13:40,047
...try to cherish her more.

192
00:13:49,877 --> 00:13:51,187
Please.

193
00:13:53,093 --> 00:13:54,633
Gen-kun...

194
00:13:56,767 --> 00:14:01,197
You too Sensei, don't be so stubborn.
Just go with him so you'll feel happy.

195
00:14:01,982 --> 00:14:04,892
Just buy me some dried fish
when you get back.

196
00:14:07,247 --> 00:14:08,837
If you'll excuse me.

197
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:12,607
Don't go!

198
00:14:26,407 --> 00:14:27,427
Why...

199
00:14:27,797 --> 00:14:28,967
It's okay.

200
00:14:29,487 --> 00:14:32,827
I'm being a fool, considering how he and I both
are already past our expiration dates.

201
00:14:33,727 --> 00:14:37,647
Um, I've been hiding
something from you. Actually...

202
00:14:37,647 --> 00:14:41,597
You're a Yakuza, aren't you? No matter
how much I look, I can't see you as
anything more than a respectable man.

203
00:14:43,127 --> 00:14:45,147
You really don't mind if I am one?

204
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:49,010
In return, please stay with me tonight.

205
00:14:49,340 --> 00:14:49,890
Huh?

206
00:14:50,854 --> 00:14:55,134
I was going to hold off until tomorrow,
but I don't have a lot of time left so...

207
00:14:55,701 --> 00:14:57,071
Let's enjoy it to the fullest.

208
00:15:00,427 --> 00:15:01,407
Okay.

209
00:15:11,843 --> 00:15:14,723
When I dropped out of high school to go to Tokyo...

210
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:21,665
Sensei's farewell words to me then were
"Come back a good man."

211
00:15:22,256 --> 00:15:23,966
She's a good teacher, huh.

212
00:15:26,727 --> 00:15:34,907
She then gave me her own lunch pack
and told me to eat it in the train.

213
00:15:38,966 --> 00:15:41,276
There were other dishes in it but...

214
00:15:42,723 --> 00:15:48,223
This dish's sweet and salty taste
was the only one that stuck with me...

215
00:15:56,257 --> 00:15:57,447
I...

216
00:15:59,944 --> 00:16:04,244
...want to quit the yakuza
and make her happy.

217
00:16:08,858 --> 00:16:11,458
After I confided to Aniki...

218
00:16:11,607 --> 00:16:14,007
...he punched me in the face and
told me that it's the other way around.

219
00:16:14,871 --> 00:16:19,471
That, "The woman's the one
who'll make YOU happy."

220
00:16:20,696 --> 00:16:25,346
She's leaving tomorrow, right?
Have you told her how you feel?

221
00:16:32,871 --> 00:16:34,331
But...

222
00:16:36,449 --> 00:16:39,329
I don't want to become
just another memory for her.

223
00:16:45,593 --> 00:16:46,753
Welcome.

224
00:16:46,753 --> 00:16:48,713
Sorry to keep you waiting.

225
00:16:48,713 --> 00:16:50,233
That's just between us, okay?

226
00:16:54,073 --> 00:16:56,113
What? What were you talking about?

227
00:16:56,513 --> 00:16:58,953
More importantly,
how's your friend doing?

228
00:16:58,953 --> 00:16:59,753
Huh?

229
00:16:59,753 --> 00:17:04,333
Didn't you say you paid a visit to a friend
of yours who's hospitalized. Is she okay?

230
00:17:04,333 --> 00:17:08,523
Yeah, I was surprised to see how
healthy she was. She'll be discharged next month.

231
00:17:09,073 --> 00:17:12,482
Oh, that's great. Let's toast to it then.

232
00:17:12,482 --> 00:17:15,563
Master, give us two glasses of beer.

233
00:17:15,685 --> 00:17:17,093
Will you be okay?

234
00:17:17,083 --> 00:17:20,363
Not drinking at an auspicious occasion,
what good is a man if he doesn't drink
in celebration of something.

235
00:17:25,171 --> 00:17:28,611
When are you coming back again?

236
00:17:31,404 --> 00:17:32,884
Not sure.

237
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:38,690
Gen-chan's gonna be lonely.

238
00:17:43,113 --> 00:17:45,343
Can I have a smoke?

239
00:17:52,365 --> 00:17:57,315
Over in the US, I heard that
it's frowned upon if you're a smoker.

240
00:17:57,993 --> 00:18:01,003
I tried quitting when I went there,
but it doesn't matter anymore.

241
00:18:10,850 --> 00:18:13,260
I can't remember anymore.

242
00:18:13,995 --> 00:18:18,765
That time when I met him here, if he didn't
say he's Gen-kun, I wouldn't have remembered.

243
00:18:20,779 --> 00:18:24,411
Are you planning to stay in the US forever?

244
00:18:24,913 --> 00:18:29,413
No. This time, I'm going some place
farther away.

245
00:18:34,070 --> 00:18:39,180
That's why I hope Gen-kun
will forget about me.

246
00:18:50,909 --> 00:18:53,989
Hey, Gen-kun... Let's go.

247
00:19:18,253 --> 00:19:19,753
Goodbye.

248
00:19:38,253 --> 00:19:41,163
He was working earnestly when
I sneaked a look today.

249
00:19:42,096 --> 00:19:45,526
Never expected he'd quit
the life of a gangster.

250
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:48,530
Isn't it almost a month by now?

251
00:19:51,345 --> 00:19:55,055
I too want to have a love
that's worth changing his life for me.

252
00:19:56,192 --> 00:19:58,982
In that case, eat this, Saya-chan.

253
00:20:01,466 --> 00:20:03,376
If this is the answer to
my prayer, it'll do but...

254
00:21:04,593 --> 00:21:12,433
(Note: Gen most likely asked here: "She's dead?"
Also, he's wearing the towel / head scarf
his teacher gave him)

